extracted_information: The project '3D Art Gallery Online' is an online 3D art gallery. It utilizes Three.js for 3D rendering and Cannon.js for physics simulation. The project structure comprises `index.html` (main HTML), `main.js` (JavaScript logic for Three.js and Cannon.js), `style.css` (basic styling), `README.md`, and an `images` folder. Dependencies, Three.js and Cannon.js, are loaded via CDN, eliminating the need for local installation. The primary technologies used are JavaScript (97.6%), HTML (1.8%), and CSS (0.6%). To run the project, a modern web browser supporting WebGL is required; execution involves simply opening the `index.html` file. The last recorded commit for the project was on June 10, 2025.

specifications.execution_environment: Modern web browser with WebGL support
